This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing tasks such as dependency parsing. Additionally, the use of bidirectional-LSTMs (BiLSTMs) is a common technique in NLP and falls under the scope of cs.CL. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the use of BiLSTMs as feature extractors could also fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper's application to image captioning tasks could potentially place it in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
